                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4397: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-30T17:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 30, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>It appears that Wu Pei-fu’s adherents gaining control North Manchuria. Local
                    Chinese military insist that Japanese aiding mutineers. Reported local Chinese
                    merchants favor Wu.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
